This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models for agglutinative languages. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for language modeling using embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural networks for language modeling. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new neural network architecture. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with syllables and their use in language modeling.
